		<h1 class="subTitle">Dell Scholars Program</h1>

		<table class="table">
			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Who Can Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">Attendees of <a href="https://www.dellscholars.org/scholarship/crps/">these CRPs</a> who are eligible for the pell grant and have at least a 2.4 GPA.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">When Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">Applications open on <b>October 1st</b> and close on <b>December 1st.</b></td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">How Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">All applicants submit an online application with a few essays. Semifinialists submit high school transcripts, their FAFSA Student Aid Report (SAR), and a recommendation.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">What Do They Get</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">Up to $20,000, a laptop, textbook credits, career counseling,  and financial aid counseling.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Successful Essay</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">N/A</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Website Link</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label"><a href="https://www.dellscholars.org/scholarship/">dellscholars.org/scholarship</a></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

		<h1 class="subTitle">Gates Scholarship (formerly Gates Millennium)</h1>

		<table class="table">
			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Who Can Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">High school seniors of color who demonstrate eligible for the pell grant and have at least a 3.3 GPA.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">When Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">Applications open on <b>July 15th</b> and close on <b>September 18th.</b></td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">How Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">All applicants submit an online application with a high school transcript and community service form. Semifinalists submit an additional online application, essays, an updated transcript, and letters of recommendation. Finalists have an interview.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">What Do They Get</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">The full cost of attendence that isn't already covered by other financial aid to any university they can get into.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Successful Essay</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label"><a href="https://ngocnhile.wordpress.com/gmsp2/">ngocnhile.wordpress.com/gmsp2</a></td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Website Link</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label"><a href="https://www.thegatesscholarship.org/scholarship">thegatesscholarship.org/scholarship</a></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

		<h1 class="subTitle">Gordon A. Rich Memorial Foundation</h1>

		<table class="table">
			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Who Can Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">High school seniors with at least a 3.5 GPA who are in the top 20% of their class and demonstrate financial need. Their parents must be full-time employees in the financial services industry.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">When Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">Applications open on <b>September 15th</b> and close on <b>February 20th.</b></td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">How Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">All applicants submit an online application with an essay, transcript, and letter of recommendation.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">What Do They Get</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">Up to $50,000 and access to GAR scholars network.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Successful Essay</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">N/A</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Website Link</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label"><a href="http://www.gordonrich.org/html/index.html">gordonrich.org</a></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

		<h1 class="subTitle">Greenhouse Scholars Program</h1>

		<table class="table">
			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Who Can Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">High school seniors who are residents of Colorado, Georgia, Illinois, or North Carolina. They must have at least a 3.5 GPA, community service interests, and demonstrated financial need.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">When Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">Applications open on <b>September 1st</b> and close on <b>December 17th.</b></td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">How Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">All applicants submit an online application. Finalists submit a headshot photo and additional application material before having an in-person interview.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">What Do They Get</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">Up to $20,000 and eligibility to apply for $2,000 grants.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Successful Essay</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">N/A</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Website Link</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label"><a href="https://greenhousescholars.org/">greenhousescholars.org</a></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

		<h1 class="subTitle">Hadden Scholarship</h1>

		<table class="table">
			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Who Can Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">High school seniors with at least a 3.5 GPA and demonstrated financial need.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">When Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">Applications open on <b>January 21st</b> and close on <b>February 28th.</b></td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">How Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">All applicants submit an online application with standardized test scores, transcripts, class standings, financial documents, an essay, and two letters of recommendation. Interview may be required.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">What Do They Get</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">Up to $16,000.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Successful Essay</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">N/A</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Website Link</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label"><a href="http://fdnweb.org/youthfdn/">fdnweb.org/youthfdn</a></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

		<h1 class="subTitle">Horatio Alger National Scholarship</h1>

		<table class="table">
			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Who Can Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">High school seniors with at least a 2.0 GPA and demonstrated financial need.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">When Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">Applications open on <b>August 1st</b> and close on <b>October 25th.</b></td>
			</tr>


			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">How Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">All applicants submit an online application.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">What Do They Get</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">$25,000 and an all-expenses paid trip to Washington, D.C. to receive their award.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Successful Essay</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">N/A</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Website Link</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label"><a href="https://scholars.horatioalger.org/scholarships/about-our-scholarship-programs/national-scholarships/">scholars.horatioalger.org</a></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

		<h1 class="subTitle">Jack Kent Cooke Foundation</h1>

		<table class="table">
			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Who Can Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">High school seniors with at least a 3.5 GPA, 1200 SAT or 26 ACT composite, and demonstrated financial need.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">When Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">Applications open on <b>September 6th</b> and close on <b>November 20th.</b></td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">How Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">All applicants submit an online application via the common app.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">What Do They Get</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">Up to $160,000 and access to the JKC scholars network.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Successful Essay</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">N/A</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Website Link</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label"><a href="https://www.jkcf.org/our-scholarships/college-scholarship-program/">jkcf.org</a></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

		<h1 class="subTitle">QuestBridge Scholars Program</h1>

		<table class="table">
			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Who Can Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">There are no strict cut-offs for QuestBrige. However, finalists generally have primarily A's in the hardest classes available, graduate at the top 5-10% of their class, have SAT/PSAT scores > 1310 and ACT composites > 28, and demonstrate significant financial need.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">When Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">Applications open <b>in the Summer</b> and close on <b>September 27th.</b></td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">How Do They Apply</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">All applicants submit an application with financial documents, essays, standardized test scores, and letters of recommendation. Finalists may be required to submit additional material if their desired schools require it.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">What Do They Get</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label">The full cost of attendence that isn't already covered by other financial aid to any QuestBridge university they match to. Additionally, their application fees are waived.</td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Successful Essay</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label"><a href="https://sites.google.com/site/qbessays/">https://sites.google.com/site/qbessays/</a></td>
			</tr>

			<tr>
				<td class="table-active label" scope="row">Website Link</td>
		  		<td class="table-active label"><a href="https://www.questbridge.org/">questbridge.org</a></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

